docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:61:- 002F completed the role-aware shell hardening: `PAGE_PERMISSIONS` and `resolveNavigationAttempt()` now live in `sfpcl-lms/src/services/navigationPermissions.ts`, `Sidebar.tsx` exports the canonical staff nav table for parity tests, and `App.tsx` uses the shared guard helper. Frontend tests assert every non-dashboard staff nav item is gated by the same prototype permission as its page, blocked navigation returns to Dashboard with `blockedPage`, `tracer.lifecycle.run` maps only to `run_tracer`, and unknown/empty-role current-user responses stay neutral. The 002EY `auth-negative` Playwright spec was extended for zero-permission, tracer-only, and invalid stored-session restore checks; local browser execution remained blocked by sandbox localhost `EPERM`.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:65:  - 002F2 must replace the shallow 002F navigation visibility test with behavior-level coverage of the actual Sidebar visibility path and route guard for zero-permission, tracer-only, unknown-role, and future admin-management navigation.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:69:- 002F2 completed the shallow Sidebar visibility corrective slice: `visibleStaffNavItems()` now lives in `sfpcl-lms/src/services/navigationPermissions.ts`, `Sidebar` consumes it with `allNavItems`, and vitest covers the actual visibility path plus direct route guard behavior for every protected item, zero-permission backend sessions, unknown/empty-role backend sessions, and tracer-only sessions. `tracer.lifecycle.run` still maps only to `run_tracer` and unlocks only Dashboard + Tracer.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:72:- For 002H: keep the workflow guard foundation domain-neutral. A shared backend transition guard may define from-state, to-state, required permission, action code, and audit/workflow-event metadata, but must not encode loan eligibility, sanction authority, money amounts, or document-completeness rules. Migrate only the existing tracer transition proof to the shared guard and preserve its public endpoint behavior and `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION` / `403 PERMISSION_DENIED` envelopes.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:74:- 002H completed the shared workflow guard foundation. `sfpcl_credit/workflows/guard.py` defines domain-neutral transition definitions/results plus typed errors for unknown action, missing permission, and invalid state. Tracer services now pass explicit actor permission codes into the shared guard for lifecycle actions while preserving existing tracer URLs, success payloads, `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`, audit logs, and workflow events. No schema change.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:78:- 002J completed the test-only API contract assertion harness. `sfpcl_credit/tests/api_contracts.py` provides assertions for success envelopes, error envelopes, top-level list pagination, and §44 target `available_actions` item shape. Regression tests cover `/auth/me/` success, admin users pagination, `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`, revoked-session `401 INVALID_TOKEN`, no-permission `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, create-only partial-admin update denial `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, and tracer `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`. No public endpoint, schema change, production import, or frontend change. A-016 records that current `/auth/me/` still returns flat permission-code strings for `available_actions`; the object item shape is asserted only against an internal target-contract sample for future detail endpoints.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:79:- 002K completed the guarded local/dev demo staff seed. `seed_demo_users` refuses unless `SFPCL_DEBUG=true` and `SFPCL_ALLOW_DEMO_SEED=true`, calls `seed_catalogue()`, and idempotently creates/updates only `demo.*@sfpcl.example` users: system admin (`system_admin`/IT), credit manager (`credit_manager`/Credit Assessment), compliance (`compliance_team_member`/Compliance), treasury (`senior_manager_finance`/Treasury), internal auditor (`internal_auditor`/Audit), tracer-only (`sales_team_user`/Sales with only A-011 `tracer.lifecycle.run`), and zero-permission (`management_viewer`, no team, no permissions). Demo users authenticate through real `/auth/login/` + `/auth/me`; tests cover guard refusal, idempotency, no `e2e.*` changes, active memberships, system-admin user-admin permissions without `manage_users`, tracer-only exact permissions, zero-permission neutral payload, auth login/logout audit rows, admin update `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, and 002J success/error/pagination contracts. No schema, frontend, auth bypass, or broad permission alias change.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:80:- Architecture review is due after 002K by cadence (`slices_completed_since_architecture_review` reaches 4). 003A has already been sharpened to add only a protected paginated `GET /api/v1/audit-logs/` over the existing `identity.AuditLog` model, using `audit.audit_log.read` as the narrowest existing audit-read permission. 003B has been sharpened to reconcile the pre-existing tracer-owned `workflow_events` table before creating/owning any canonical workflow-event foundation.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:83:- Endpoints implemented under `/api/v1/tracer/`: create member, create application, sanction, create account, disburse, post repayment, close.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:85:- Guardrails tested: positive amounts only; invalid state transitions return `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`; missing bearer auth returns `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`; revoked access sessions return `401 INVALID_TOKEN`; authenticated users without `tracer.lifecycle.run` return `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`; zero-permission/unmapped frontend roles do not map tracer permissions.
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:40:| Early end-to-end tracer | Implemented in slice 002EX | Staff Tracer screen | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §3-6; `docs/source/data-model.md` §26.1-26.2 | Thin dev proof only. Protected by session-bound bearer auth and explicit `tracer.lifecycle.run` permission. Endpoints: `POST /api/v1/tracer/members/`, `POST /api/v1/tracer/members/{member_id}/loan-applications/`, `POST /api/v1/tracer/loan-applications/{loan_application_id}/sanction/`, `POST /api/v1/tracer/loan-applications/{loan_application_id}/loan-account/`, `POST /api/v1/tracer/loan-accounts/{loan_account_id}/disburse/`, `POST /api/v1/tracer/loan-accounts/{loan_account_id}/repayments/`, `POST /api/v1/tracer/loan-accounts/{loan_account_id}/close/`. Minimal models only; every transition writes `audit_logs` and `workflow_events`; invalid state transitions return `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`; missing/revoked auth returns the standard `401` envelope before domain writes. |
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:41:| API contract test harness | Implemented in slice 002J | None | `api-contracts.md` §6.1-6.4, §7.1-7.3, §44 | Test-only assertions live in `sfpcl_credit/tests/api_contracts.py`. Future endpoint slices should use them to prove standard success envelopes, error envelopes, top-level list pagination, and target §44 `available_actions` item shapes without importing test utilities from production code. The harness regression tests cover `/auth/me/`, admin users pagination, `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`, revoked-session `401 INVALID_TOKEN`, `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, partial-admin write denial, and tracer `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`. A-016 records that current `/auth/me/` still returns flat permission-code strings for `available_actions`; the object shape is asserted against an internal sample for future detail endpoints. |
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:42:| Local demo staff seed | Implemented in slice 002K | Login, dashboard smoke, admin/tracer permission smoke | `implementation-roadmap.md` §10, §20-22; `technical-architecture.md` §8-12, §17-18; `auth-permissions.md`; `api-contracts.md` §11-12, §43-44 | `python manage.py seed_demo_users` is a guarded local/dev seed path. It refuses unless `SFPCL_DEBUG=true` and `SFPCL_ALLOW_DEMO_SEED=true`, calls `seed_catalogue()`, creates or updates deterministic `demo.*@sfpcl.example` staff users with active primary roles and memberships, and does not alter `e2e.*` users. Demo users authenticate through the real `/auth/login/` and `/auth/me/` endpoints; there is no demo auth bypass. The zero-permission user returns `permissions: []` and `available_actions: []`; the tracer-only user returns only `tracer.lifecycle.run`; system admin preserves canonical action-specific user-admin permissions without broad `manage_users` aliases. |
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:72:## Early tracer API (002EX)
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:74:The 002EX tracer is a deliberately thin integration proof, not the final member/application/finance contract. It follows the source API rules for versioning, envelopes, explicit action endpoints, backend-enforced transitions, and audit/workflow observability.
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:79:- The authenticated user's effective permission list must include `tracer.lifecycle.run`; otherwise the API returns `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`.
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:82:- Every successful transition writes one `audit_logs` row whose action starts with `tracer.` and one `workflow_events` row.
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:84:Response examples for login, `/auth/me`, every tracer transition, and persistent SQLite counts are saved in `.ralph/runs/2026-07-03_234219_normal_run/api-response-samples.md`.
docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md:164:- Roles with no seeded production permission links, including the A-007 `sales_team_user`, `it_head`, and `management_viewer` cases, return an empty permission list until source documents define grants. The guarded local/demo `seed_demo_users` command is the narrow exception: in a local demo database it grants `tracer.lifecycle.run` to the demo tracer user's existing `sales_team_user` role per A-011.
